This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it focuses on the optimization and search technique based on the principles of genetics and natural selection. Additionally, it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as GAs are commonly used in these fields. The Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also a possibility as GAs can be used for system optimization. Finally, the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper discusses different crossover operators used in GAs for solving problems.
